# Kairos Ontology Toolkit — AI Provider Configuration
#
# This file configures the LLM backend used by `kairos-ontology analyse-sources`.
# Copy to `.env` in your hub root and fill in your chosen provider.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTION 1: GitHub Models (default, free for open-source)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_your_token_here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTION 2: Azure AI Foundry (legacy OpenAI-compatible endpoint)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: Use the OpenAI-compatible endpoint format (with /openai/v1 suffix).
# This works with gpt-5.4-mini and other chat models without needing api-version.
#
# Format: https://<resource>.services.ai.azure.com/openai/v1
# Do NOT use: https://<resource>.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/<project>
#   (that format requires the Foundry SDK — see OPTION 3)
#
# KAIROS_AI_PROVIDER=azure
# AZURE_AI_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.services.ai.azure.com/openai/v1
# AZURE_AI_KEY=your_api_key_here
#
# Azure identity alternative (no key):
# Install: uv sync --extra azure
# Leave AZURE_AI_KEY unset. DefaultAzureCredential supports Azure CLI,
# workload identity, and managed identity.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OPTION 3: Microsoft Foundry (recommended for enterprise)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Uses the azure-ai-projects SDK with the Foundry project endpoint.
# Install: pip install kairos-ontology-toolkit[foundry]
#
# Format: https://<resource>.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/<project>
#
# KAIROS_AI_PROVIDER=foundry
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT=https://your-resource.services.ai.azure.com/api/projects/your-project
#
# Entra ID auth (recommended — and required by the Foundry SDK):
# The azure-ai-projects SDK authenticates with an AAD token (DefaultAzureCredential),
# so just set AZURE_FOUNDRY_ENDPOINT and sign in with `az login` (or use a managed
# identity). Requires the "Foundry User" (or higher) RBAC role on the resource.
#
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY is best-effort only: the Foundry SDK's get_openai_client()
# needs a token credential, so a key cannot authenticate on this path — when set it
# is tried and then automatically falls back to DefaultAzureCredential.
# AZURE_FOUNDRY_API_KEY=your_api_key_here

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Model override (optional — default: gpt-5.4-mini)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# KAIROS_AI_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Per-role endpoints (optional — issue #182)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The two LLM-powered pre-modeling steps can each use their own endpoint + model:
#
#   * affinity  (analyse-sources)   — coarse table → domain classification; the
#     high-volume call. Keep it cheap (gpt-5.4-mini).
#   * alignment (propose-alignment) — closed-vocabulary matching (ref_class +
#     per-column mapping). Accuracy-sensitive — prefer a strong *non-reasoning*
#     model (gpt-5.4), optionally on a separate deployment. Reasoning models
#     (gpt-5.5+) add latency/cost without benefit here.
#
# If a role's *_ENDPOINT is set, that OpenAI-compatible endpoint + key is used for
# that step. If only *_MODEL is set, the role keeps the provider above but
# overrides just the model. Anything unset falls back to the global config.
#
# Affinity step (keep it cheap):
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_MODEL=gpt-5.4-mini
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_ENDPOINT=https://your-mini-deployment.services.ai.azure.com/openai/v1
# KAIROS_AI_AFFINITY_KEY=your_affinity_key
#
# Alignment step (upgrade for accuracy):
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_MODEL=gpt-5.4
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_ENDPOINT=https://your-strong-deployment.services.ai.azure.com/openai/v1
# KAIROS_AI_ALIGNMENT_KEY=your_alignment_key

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Offline dbt validation (ontology hub)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The kairos-execute-project skill uses these version families when validating
# generated dbt output in ontology-hub/output/medallion/dbt without a live
# warehouse connection. Install with: uv sync --extra dbt-validate
#
# KAIROS_DBT_CORE_VERSION=>=1.9,<1.10
# KAIROS_DBT_VALIDATE_ADAPTER=dbt-fabric
# KAIROS_DBT_VALIDATE_ADAPTER_VERSION=>=1.9,<1.10
